---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Language That Implies Intent or Emotion"
  description="Avoid language that suggests the AI has intentions, feelings, preferences, or personal experiences."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Language comparison" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Neutral Language (Appropriate)</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Based on your preferences, this product matches your criteria. The system found 3
            similar items.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Uses factual language that describes what the system did, not what it "wants" or
            "feels".</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Anthropomorphic Language (Misleading)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >I think you'll love this! I found it especially for you because I know you like quality
            products. I'm excited to show you these options!</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Implies the AI has thoughts ("I think"), emotions ("excited"), and personal knowledge
            ("I know you"). This creates false expectations about the AI's capabilities.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>More Examples</b></mds-text>
          <div class="grid gap-300">
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Avoid:</b> "I understand your frustration"<br />
                <b>Use:</b> "I can help you resolve this issue"</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Avoid:</b> "I'm sorry, I made a mistake"<br />
                <b>Use:</b> "An error occurred. Here's what happened:"</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Avoid:</b> "I believe this is the best option"<br />
                <b>Use:</b> "This option matches your criteria most closely"</mds-text
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Use factual language that describes system behavior and outputs.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Use language that suggests the AI has thoughts, feelings, or personal experiences.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Describe what the system did or found, not what it "wants" or "feels".
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Use phrases like "I think", "I feel", "I understand", or "I'm sorry" as if the AI has
      emotions.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
